# Integrate a Magic Patterns Design

Magic Patterns generates **prototypes**. Treat exported code as a design spec (layout, hierarchy, spacing, interactions), not production code to paste verbatim.

**Golden rule:** when the Magic Patterns code and this codebase disagree, **the codebase wins**.

## This project

- Next.js App Router, React, Tailwind v4
- Wedding invitation templates live in `templates/` with shared primitives in `templates/shared/`
- Admin UI in `components/admin/` — match existing card, form, and nav patterns
- Reuse template section components (`OpeningBlock`, `EventDetails`, `RsvpForm`, etc.) instead of duplicating UI
- Match existing color tokens, typography (`font-display`, `text-muted`, `bg-card`), and spacing

## Workflow

1. Read the Magic Patterns design (via MCP URL or exported files). Identify screens, components, states, and mock data shapes.
2. Survey this repo: find the closest existing template or admin page and use it as the structural template.
3. Map prototype elements to codebase equivalents (buttons, inputs, cards, icons, routing).
4. Implement in the correct folder (`templates/<name>/components/` or `components/admin/`), wire real data, discard Vite scaffolding and mock data.
5. Verify against the design for intent (not pixel-perfect arbitrary values) and run `npm run build`.

## Discard from exports

- Vite scaffolding (`vite.config.ts`, `index.html`, root `package.json`)
- Prototype `tailwind.config.js` / global CSS — merge only genuinely new tokens
- `data-id` props, `utils/mockData.ts`, editor preview files
- New dependencies (lucide-react, framer-motion) unless already in this project
